<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <title>Catalog Service - Design Document</title>
  <style>body{font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif} h1{color:#2b6cb0}</style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Catalog Service — High Level Design</h1>
  <p>Version: 0.2</p>
  <h2>Overview 🧭</h2>
  <p>The Catalog Service manages product master data, categories, variants, attributes, media, publishing workflow, audit, and eventing. Designed as a modular monolith with microservice-ready boundaries.</p>

  <h2>Goals & Non-Goals ✅ / ❌</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Support product CRUD, publish workflow, categories, attributes, media (initial subset implemented)</li>
    <li>Provide read-optimized APIs and event publishing via outbox → Kafka</li>
    <li>Non-goal: full UI, payment, or order processing</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Architecture (HLD) 🗂️</h2>
  <p>Logical components:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>API Layer (Spring MVC controllers)</li>
    <li>Security Layer (JWT / Stubbed header auth)</li>
    <li>Service Layer (business logic, validations)</li>
    <li>Repository Layer (JPA/Hibernate)</li>
    <li>Outbox/Event Publisher (reliable eventing)</li>
    <li>Read model / caching (Redis) — planned</li>
    <li>Database (Postgres production, H2 for local dev)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Deployment</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Single Spring Boot jar per service/module</li>
    <li>Flyway for schema migrations</li>
    <li>External services: Postgres, Redis, Kafka</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Component Diagram (textual) 🧩</h2>
  <pre>
  [Client] -> [API Controller] -> [Service Layer] -> [Repository (JPA) -> Postgres]
                                              -> [Outbox Table] -> [Outbox Publisher] -> Kafka
                                              -> [Redis Cache] (read-optimized)
  </pre>

  <h2>Class Diagram (summary)</h2>
  <p>Key domain classes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Product (id, sku, name, description, status, version, createdBy, createdAt, updatedAt)</li>
    <li>Category (id, name, slug, description, parentId, active)</li>
    <li>ProductCategoryMap (id, productId, categoryId)</li>
    <li>AttributeDefinition, ProductAttribute, Variant, MediaAsset (planned)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Flows & Sequence Diagrams</h2>
  <h3>Product Create</h3>
  <pre>
  Client -> POST /catalog/products
    Controller validates DTO
    -> Service creates Product (optimistic locking version=1)
    -> Repository saves
    -> Service writes Outbox event (ProductCreated)
    -> Response 200 with ProductDto
  </pre>

  <h3>Assign Category to Product</h3>
  <pre>
  Client -> POST /catalog/products/{productId}/categories/{categoryId}
    Controller -> Service.addCategoryToProduct
      Service checks product & category exist
      Service inserts into product_category_map (idempotent)
      (optionally) writes outbox event ProductCategoryAssigned
    Response 200
  </pre>

  <h2>Database Schema (high level)</h2>
  <pre>
  users(id, username, password, role_id)
  roles(id, name)
  products(id, sku, name, description, status, version, created_by, created_at, updated_at)
  categories(id, name, slug, description, parent_id, active, created_by, created_at, updated_at)
  product_category_map(id, product_id, category_id)
  attribute_definitions(...)
  product_attributes(...)
  product_variants(...)
  media_assets(...)
  outbox_events(id, aggregate_type, aggregate_id, type, payload, processed)
  audit_log(id, entity_type, entity_id, action, actor, timestamp, before_snapshot, after_snapshot)
  </pre>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>Initial implementation uses a stubbed header X-User: username:ROLE1,ROLE2. Later replace with JWT filter. Role-based checks enforced in service/controller layers.</p>

  <h2>Observability & Logging</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Structured logging (key=value) via Logback</li>
    <li>Metrics endpoints (Actuator) — to be enabled</li>
    <li>Correlation ID header propagated across services</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Extensibility</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Modular packages per domain (catalog, security, outbox, audit)</li>
    <li>Services designed to be extracted as microservices</li>
    <li>Use DTOs and mappers to decouple persistence models from API</li>
  </ul>

